description.plain:
Miles Parks McCollum (born August 23, 1997, in Mableton, Georgia), popularly known as Lil Yachty, is an American rapper and singer from Atlanta, Georgia. He’s known for his comical lyrics and unique melodies—not to mention his cherry-red hair.

Yachty was rocketed into the spotlight in 2016, when “1Night” from his Summer Songs EP, went viral after it was used in a comedy sketch. Soon after, Yachty released his Lil Boat mixtape—which features an extended version of “1Night,” along with a remix of “Minnesota” with Young Thug, Quavo, and Skippa Da Flippa.

Signed to Migos‘ management team Quality Control, Yachty uses Atlanta’s signature trap-flavored beats, along with his unique auto-tuned vocals. His Lil Boat mixtape identity switches between light-hearted, melodic Lil Yachty, and the deft emcee Lil Boat.

Yachty continued to dominate summer 2016 with Summer Songs 2, the follow-up to the original EP. In the following years, he released his debut album Teenage Emotions., followed by other mixtapes and albums Lil Boat 2, Nuthin' 2 Prove, and Lil Boat 3.

songs.title: Peek a Boo

description.plain:
Before releasing it in its entirety, Lil Yachty debuted a 10 second snippet of this song on his Instagram on February 28, 2017. He later went on to release a 30 second snippet of the song on his Twitter on March 2, 2017.

On the day of dropping this track Lil Yachty appeared on Power 105.1, expressing his motivation for making this song:

You know what my main focus was this year? Not even this year but just like, in life.  I don’t go to clubs but every time I go to the club…my shit never sounds right in the club…I wanted to make a song that sounded right…So I made the song that I dropped today, just for the club.

songs.title: One Night

description.plain:
“One Night” finds Lil Yachty telling a girl the only thing she’ll ever be to him is a one night stand.

The song became a SoundCloud hit after it was used in a late 2015 viral comedy sketch.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pLMuQnBvx7U

During an annotation session with Genius, Yachty claimed he had reached out to the video’s creator, SenseiLeFox, to thank him for using the song in his skit. Yachty went on to talk about the making of the song:

We made “1Night” about six, seven months ago. I made that song in high school. [The Good Perry] sent me the beat when I was on my way to the studio and I wrote it in like five minutes. It just came to me instantly. It was really a snippet but we just liked it so much.
